imdb.plot outline: In celebration of Black History Month, TV One is debuting Change Agents: History in the Making, 21 short films produced by four award-winning content creators - American Black Film Festival winner Alton Glass (CRU); Jeanine Daniels, acclaimed director, producer, writer and actress of wildly popular web series The Guy on Black&Sexy TV and creator of The Couple for the preceding network, which is now in development at HBO; NAACP Image Award winner P. Frank Williams (Unsung); and Grammy, Golden Globe and Academy Award winner Rhymefest (co-writer "Jesus Walks" and "Glory").

plot: In celebration of Black History Month, TV One is debuting _Change Agents: History in the Making_ (qv), 21 short films produced by four award-winning content creators - American Black Film Festival winner Alton Glass (CRU); Jeanine Daniels, acclaimed director, producer, writer and actress of wildly popular web series The Guy on Black&Sexy TV and creator of The Couple for the preceding network, which is now in development at HBO; NAACP Image Award winner P. Frank Williams (Unsung); and Grammy, Golden Globe and Academy Award winner Rhymefest (co-writer "Jesus Walks" and "Glory").::T. Pryor
